    backupPlan:
      'External funding is essential for several reasons, but most importantly because it will enable me to conduct fieldwork during the summer months in Southern Africa (December-February). Under my contract as a TA, I am obligated to teach during this period for the entirety of my PhD. To carry out fieldwork in that time, I therefore need funding that can cover the fees of registering as in absentia for a full quarter, as well as funding that can cover the lost income I would otherwise receive from my teaching stipend. I unfortunately still would need to pay rent and car insurance when I’m gone, hence the importance of that supplement.\n\nIf I don’t get ACXG funding, I can still manage to get to Lesotho during my winter break, then come back to the United States to fulfill my responsibilities as a TA. But this period is too early to guarantee that mushrooms would be growing and in active use, since the rainy season doesn’t always kick in until January. It is is also much shorter than I would ideally need for traveling to Lesotho, then within the country — especially given that healers are not always amenable to a preordained schedule — and then to the institutions in South Africa that can process physical samples. Without funding, then, there is a relatively high chance that the research period would end up being too short and/or mistimed.',
