      'So far, our experiments have been funded by Dillon’s postdoc advisor. However, that funding is running out (and Adam’s advisor does not have money available to spend on AI research). Hence, we are applying for funding now.\n\nDillon has applied for larger grants from Open Philanthropy and Longview to fund his ongoing postdoc salary, and those grants would include funds for research. Hence, if those grants come through, we would have other sources of funding for this research. If Dillon gets hired at Anthropic, it is possible (but uncertain) that he could continue this work there, in which case we would no longer need ACX funds. If he could not, Adam could continue this work without him using ACX funds. \n\nOtherwise, without the ACX grant, we may be able to run around one more study using Dillon’s advisor’s funds, but we would likely not be able to run the ambitious studies described here unless we found another funding source.',
